Vendored reference code and data for the `fdid_hongkong` benchmark.

Files
  Fun_FDID.R   Kathleen T. Li's Forward DiD function (forward control selection,
               DiD estimation, and inference).
  GDP.csv      Hong Kong quarterly GDP-growth panel: Hong Kong (treated, column 1)
               and 24 control economies. The publicly available dataset of
               Hsiao, Ching & Wan (2012), "A panel data approach for program
               evaluation," Journal of Applied Econometrics 27(5), 705-740.

Source
  Released replication package for
    Li, Kathleen T. (2024), "Forward Difference-in-Differences,"
    Marketing Science. DOI: 10.1287/mksc.2022.0212
  The author distributes this MATLAB/R code and the public Hong Kong dataset for
  replication of the Forward DiD method. Vendored here verbatim so the reference
  run is reproducible offline; all credit to the author. See the package's
  ForwardDID_Readme.txt for the author's own sample output.

These files are used only to produce the captured reference bundle that
mlsynth's FDID estimator is cross-validated against; they are not part of the
mlsynth library.
